"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792616","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-23","<p>The £2.3 billion Housing Infrastructure Fund, extended by an additional £2.7 billion at Autumn Budget 2017, will unlock homes in areas of greatest housing need. It is an open and competitive fund, available for all local authorities to put forward their ambitious plans for housing growth.</p><p>We want the Housing Infrastructure Fund to support the delivery of as many homes as possible. Therefore, we are not prescribing the final split between the two funding streams, or pre-determining the distribution of funding according to region. We are currently assessing bids from local authorities. However, if higher ranked local authority bids are ineligible or have been rejected, we will consider the local authorities lower ranked bids.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792616/answer",,,,,"114541 ; 114542","2017-11-23T16:45:22.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792616/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792616/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-20","Housing Infrastructure Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether a bid for the Housing Infrastructure Fund that has been ranked lower by a local authority than a bid that is ineligible or has been rejected will still be considered.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","114543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792617","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-28","<p>There were 18 applications for the position of Government Chief Scientific Adviser.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792617/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T13:07:05.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792617/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792617/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-20","Government Chief Scientific Adviser: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many candidates were considered for the position of Chief Scientific Adviser.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792618","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-23","<p>The work of the Crown Representatives overall is seen as positive by suppliers. This view is supported by figure 8 contained within the NAO report “<em>Managing Government Suppliers</em>“ <a href="https://www.nao.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/10298-001-Governments-managing-contractors-HC-811.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.nao.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/10298-001-Governments-managing-contractors-HC-811.pdf</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792618/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T14:25:58.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792618/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792618/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-20","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what (a) qualitative and (b) quantitative information is collected on Strategic Supplier perceptions of Crown Representatives.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792619","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Government's policy relating to the risk-assessment of Strategic Suppliers is set out in the publicly available Strategic Supplier Risk Management Policy:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/80222/20121108_Strategic_Supplier_Risk_Management_Policy.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/80222/20121108_Strategic_Supplier_Risk_Management_Policy.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Cabinet Office does not publish supplier designations under the policy as &quot;high risk&quot; or risk ratings used to proactively monitor and manage Strategic Suppliers in a manner consistent with the policy, as disclosure of this information would prejudice commercial interests.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792619/answer",,,,,,"2017-12-19T15:29:35.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792619/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792619/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-20","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the National Audit Office report, Managing Government Suppliers, HC 811 of Session 2013-14, published on 11 November 2013, how many strategic suppliers to the Government have been rated as (a) green, (b) amber, (c) red and (d) black in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792620","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-27","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Article 19 of the European Trade Secrets Directive states that Member States must transpose the provisions in the Directive by 9 June 2018. The Government is working towards implementing the Directive into UK law by this date so complying with its obligations under EU law.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792620/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T11:30:11.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792620/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792620/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-20","Commercial Secrets: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the timetable is for transposing the European Trade Secrets Directive into UK law.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792621","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-11-27","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The European Trade Secrets Directive provides minimum standards concerning civil proceedings relating to measures, procedures and remedies that trade secret holders should be able to rely on in the event of unlawful acquisition, use or disclosure of their trade secrets. The Directive does not relate to the criminalisation of the misappropriation of trade secrets. Consequently, the Government does not have any plans to introduce any new criminal offence as a result of transposing the Directive into UK law.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792621/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T11:12:21.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792621/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792621/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-11-20","Commercial Secrets: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to introduce any new criminal offence in UK law as a result of the transposition into UK law of the European Trade Secrets Directive.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792622","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-29","<p>The overarching principle in all public procurement is to secure the best value for money for the taxpayer. One tool available to departments to achieve this is Open Book Contract Management (OBCM), a structured process for the sharing and management of charges and costs and operational and performance data between the supplier and the client.</p><p> </p><p>OBCM should be used on those contracts where the additional cost is justified by the perceived level of benefits and risk.</p><p> </p><p>Guidance on the use of OBCM can be found on GOV.UK:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/525283/obcm_guidance_final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/525283/obcm_guidance_final.pdf</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792622/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-29T11:16:02.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792622/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792622/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-11-20","Government Departments: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what guidance is given to departments on the size of profit margins given to private contractors when awarding contracts.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","114549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792623","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-23","<p>The government is analysing the responses to the consultation and will respond in due course.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792623/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T11:16:31.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792623/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792623/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-20","Tobacco: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he plans to publish the results of the consultation on the tax treatment of heated tobacco products.","false","Biography information for Craig Mackinlay","South Thanet","Craig Mackinlay","114550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792624","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-23","<p>The government keeps all taxes under review and considers this issue carefully at each fiscal event.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792624/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T11:20:31.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792624/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792624/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-20","Tobacco: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the point of income maximisation on tobacco excise; and what steps he plans to take in the event the point has been reached.","false","Biography information for Craig Mackinlay","South Thanet","Craig Mackinlay","114551"
