"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792767","Department of Health","false","2017-11-28","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792767/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T13:57:36.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792767/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792767/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-20","Drugs: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prisoners have been identified as suffering a drug-induced psychosis in prison in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792768","Department for Education","false","2017-11-23","<p>There are currently 7 civil servants in the department working solely on devolution of the Adult Education Budget with additional input and assistance from an additional number of people from across the department and the Education and Skills Funding Agency. It is the responsibility of each Mayoral Combined Authority and the Greater London Authority to determine their own level of resourcing.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792768/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T12:49:37.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792768/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792768/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-20","Adult Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education how many civil servants in her Department are working solely on the devolution of the adult education budget (a) in total and (b) in each mayoral or combined authority.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","114695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792769","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-28","<p>Guidance has been developed, in conjunction with Public Health England to provide information and practical advice to staff to assist with managing the potential risks associated with narcotics. There are strategies in place to reduce the supply of narcotics and detection of all psychotic substances (PS). This include the empowerment and training of staff to tackle PS use.</p><p> </p><p>We have also taken swift action to stop the supply of drugs into all our prisons, equipping all prisons with portable and fixed detectors to tackle illicit use of phones in prisons. We are working with the police to catch and convict criminal using drones to smuggle contraband into prisons, and are testing physical and technological countermeasures to stop incursions.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792769/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T17:29:33.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792769/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792769/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-20","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the implementation of a smoking ban on narcotics use in prisons.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792770","Department for Education","false","2017-11-28","<p>There are a range of digital qualifications approved for adult learners.</p><p> </p><p>Digital qualifications and the examination bodies that offer them at level 3 and above for adults are included in the Advanced Learner Loans catalogue which is published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/advanced-learner-loans-qualifications-catalogue" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/advanced-learner-loans-qualifications-catalogue</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Digital qualifications and the examination bodies that offer them at levels 2 and 3 are included in the list of qualifications which form part of the statutory entitlements for learners aged 19 to 23 which published online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/qualifications-getting-approval-for-funding" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/qualifications-getting-approval-for-funding</a>.</p><p> </p><p>There are also basic digital qualifications and units available as part of the local flexibility offer within the Adult Education Budget.</p><p> </p><p>The Digital Strategy published in March 2017 confirmed that the government will introduce an entitlement for adults who lack basic digital skills to undertake fully-funded training. The entitlement to free digital skills training for adults was provided through the Digital Economy Act 2017. This will mirror the approach taken for adult literacy and numeracy training.</p><p> </p><p>The government is currently working with Further Education institutions, employers and other stakeholders to develop the appropriate training. The department will set out specific basic digital qualifications for adult learners eligible for fully-funded training in due course.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792770/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T14:57:11.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792770/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792770/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-20","ICT: Adult Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will set out approved digital qualifications for adult learners and the examination bodies that offer them.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","114697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792771","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-24","<p>In the Prison Safety and Reform White paper published in November 2016, the Ministry of Justice committed to strengthen measures to enhance our drug testing regime in prisons, this included increasing the frequency and range of drugs tested for. Waste water testing is one of the options under consideration alongside other innovative technologies.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792771/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-24T14:46:20.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792771/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792771/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-20","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department plans to test waste water from prisons for illegal substances.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792772","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-11-24","<p>We take a zero-tolerance approach to drugs in our prisons. Anyone found with contraband will be subject to disciplinary action and police investigation. We are taking unprecedented action to stop the supply and use of drugs, including an innovative new drug testing programme and have over 300 dogs to detect psychoactive substances.</p><p> </p><p>We have also invested £3 million in enhanced intelligence, to improve our targeted intelligence and search capabilities. We are working closely with government partners to address issues with drugs at every stage of the supply chain, including those attempting to smuggle drugs into prisons.</p><p> </p><p>In this case the information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost. This is because Prison-NOMIS does not, normally, contain this data in a consistent format, and much of the data is held at a local level.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792772/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-24T14:50:15.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792772/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792772/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-11-20","Prisons: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many confiscated drugs found in prisons have been tested in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792773","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-28","<p>The Cities and Local Government Devolution Act 2016 Section 102I provides that a sub-national transport body’s transport strategy should contain its proposals for the promotion and encouragement of sustainable, safe, integrated, efficient and economic transport facilities and services to, from and within its area, as required to meet the needs of persons (including pedestrians) living, working or visiting its area and the needs of freight.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792773/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T15:58:18.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792773/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792773/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-20","Transport: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport what criteria his Department will use to assess transport strategies proposed by Transport for the North.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","114700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792774","Department of Health","false","2017-11-28","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>In February 2013, the National Offender Management Service (NOMS) (now HM Prison and Probation Service) issued guidance to prisons and immigration removal centres operated by NOMS concerning emergency ambulance call-outs. This guidance, Prison Service Instruction (PSI) 03/2013 Medical Emergency Response Codes outlines the medical symptoms in a prisoner, but not behaviours such as drug misuse, for which a prison must always call out an emergency ambulance. This PSI is mandatory in all prisons in England.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792774/answer",,,,,"114702","2017-11-28T13:30:46.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792774/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792774/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-20","Drugs: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many emergency callouts for prisoners suffering the effects of drug usage there have been (a) in each prison and (b) broken down by primary healthcare provider in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792775","Department of Health","false","2017-11-28","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>In February 2013, the National Offender Management Service (NOMS) (now HM Prison and Probation Service) issued guidance to prisons and immigration removal centres operated by NOMS concerning emergency ambulance call-outs. This guidance, Prison Service Instruction (PSI) 03/2013 Medical Emergency Response Codes outlines the medical symptoms in a prisoner, but not behaviours such as drug misuse, for which a prison must always call out an emergency ambulance. This PSI is mandatory in all prisons in England.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792775/answer",,,,,"114701","2017-11-28T13:30:46.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792775/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792775/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-20","Drugs: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on how many occasions emergency services have attended prisoners affected by illegal drug use by (a) prison and (b) primary healthcare provider in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792776","Department of Health","false","2017-11-28","<p>Information is not collected centrally on how many prisons use the National Early Warning Score to respond to symptoms of new psychoactive substances.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has not made an assessment of the effectiveness of the use of the National Early Warning Score in prisons in Liverpool.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792776/answer",,,,,"114704","2017-11-28T13:34:13.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792776/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792776/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-11-20","Drugs: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prisons use the National Early Warning Score to respond to symptoms of new psychoactive substances.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","114703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792778","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-28","<p>The Government has concerns about allegations of mistreatment of Palestinian detainees and about Israel’s respect for its relevant obligations as an Occupying Power under applicable international law. While we have not made an assessment of the humanitarian needs of Palestinian detainees, a focus of UK human rights engagement is Palestinian minors in Israeli military detention, as we have concerns about the treatment of minors during arrest and interrogation. We have raised these concerns with the Israeli authorities on many occasions, and will continue to do so.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792778/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T15:55:15.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792778/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792778/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-11-20","Palestinians: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the humanitarian needs of Palestiinian detainees in Israeli prisons.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792779","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-28","<p>The Government receives representations on a wide range of issues. It is not normal practice to release details of representations regarding specific cases.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792779/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T14:03:50.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792779/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792779/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-20","Roadchef: Employee Benefit Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has received on repayment of monies held by HM Revenue and Customs to the Roadchef Employees Benefit Trust.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","114706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792780","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>Various recent international reports (by the World Bank, the International Monetary Fund and the United Nations) continue to conclude that Israeli constraints on movement, access and trade remain a key impediment to economic growth and well-being in the Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPTs), including restricting access to land, water, and medical services and supplies. The UK continues to press for a sustainable two-state political solution which addresses Israel’s legitimate security concerns whilst opening up movement and access for Palestinians.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792780/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:09:51.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792780/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792780/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","West Bank: Travel Restrictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the economic and humanitarian effect of restrictions on the movement of Palestinian people in the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792781","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-28","<p>I refer the Hon Member to my written answer of 5 July 2017 (UIN 1465).</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792781/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T14:05:32.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792781/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792781/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-20","Employee Benefit Trusts: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will review the regulation of employee benefit trusts with reference to representations made on behalf of the Roadchef Employees Benefit Trust.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","114708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792782","HM Treasury","false","2017-11-28","The administration of the tax system, including where appropriate the repayment of tax or duties, is a matter for HM Revenue and Customs. It would not be appropriate for Treasury Ministers to become involved in specific cases.","Central Devon","Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792782/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T14:08:20.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792782/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792782/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-11-20","Tax Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer if he will issue guidance to HM Revenue and Customs on unjust enrichment as a result of the case of the Roadchef Employees Benefit Trust.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","114709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792783","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>According to the UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs, 5,513 families (some 29,000 people) were still internally displaced as a result of the Gaza-Israel hostilities in 2014 at the end of August 2017.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792783/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:10:51.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792783/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792783/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","Gaza: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many families remain displaced as a result of the Gaza-Israel hostilities in 2014.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792784","Department for Education","false","2017-11-23","<p>The Department for Education is publishing management information relating to the rollout of 30 hours free childcare in monthly management information releases. These can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/30-hours-free-childcare-eligibility-codes-issued-and-validated" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/30-hours-free-childcare-eligibility-codes-issued-and-validated</a>.</p><p>Information relating to 30 hours codes issued and validated for the spring term will be issued in a future management information release.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792784/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T09:31:17.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792784/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792784/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-20","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many 30-free hours of childcare eligibility codes have been generated for children whose first term of eligibility is the January term.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","114711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792785","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-23","<p>The Department does and will continue to provide transparency releases on gov.uk concerning the costs and details of ministerial transport on a regular basis.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Exiting the European Union ensures that all travel options are considered for overseas visits to ensure value for money and efficient use of time.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>RAF aircraft have been available to senior ministers for many years.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792785/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T14:39:30.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792785/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792785/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-11-20","Department for Exiting the European Union: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how much his Department has spent on flights for Ministers provided by RAF aircraft in each month from July 2016.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","114712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792786","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>It is critical that there is a shared understanding of progress on all the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), including SDG 5. This enables us, collectively, to take further action to have maximum development impact and reach those most at risk of being left behind. The UK Government analyses information from various sources when assessing progress on SDG 5, including the United Nations annual Sustainable Development Goals (SDG) report. We also invest in and share research that improves our understanding of the challenges in meeting SDG 5 and what works in responding to these challenges. We work with partners, for example through the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development’s DAC Network on Gender Equality, to share analysis and identify common strategies for making progress towards achieving SDG 5.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792786/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:14:17.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792786/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792786/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how the Government will analyse progress on implementing Sustainable Development Goal 5 on gender equality and women's empowerment in developing countries.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792787","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>It is critical that the experience of vulnerable and marginalised groups is included in assessments of progress on the Sustainable Development Goals, including SDG 5. DFID is supporting our UN partners to assess global progress on the SDGs accurately, by strengthening our data on vulnerable and marginalised groups. Our Data Disaggregation Action Plan, launched in early 2017, outlines our approach to ensuring we leave no one behind in our policy and programmes. This will strengthen our understanding of who, where and why people are at risk of being left behind. It will enable us to empower vulnerable and marginalised groups, and help to ensure they are included in assessments of progress and need, and in development policy and programming.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792787/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:18:53.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792787/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792787/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how the Government plans to collates data from vulnerable and marginalised groups in developing countries when evaluating their progress in implementing Sustainable Development Goal 5.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792788","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>It is critical that there is a shared understanding of progress on all the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), including SDG 5. This enables us, collectively, to take further action to have maximum development impact and reach those most at risk of being left behind. We support our UN partners to assess global progress on the SDGs accurately, by disaggregating all relevant DFID programme results and research findings by sex as well as by age, disability and location. Through our regular engagement with civil society organisations, including the Gender and Development Network of 62 non-governmental organisations, we collectively analyse progress, and identify common strategies for making progress towards achieving SDG 5.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792788/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:15:28.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792788/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792788/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government plans to consult civil society organisations about how to measure progress on Sustainable Development Goal 5 on gender equality and women's empowerment.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792789","Department for International Development","false","2017-11-27","<p>It is critical that there is a shared understanding of progress on all the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), including SDG 5. This enables us, collectively, to take further action to have maximum development impact and reach those most at risk of being left behind. We support our UN partners to assess global progress on the SDGs accurately, by disaggregating all relevant DFID programme results and research findings by sex as well as by age, disability and location. DFID is increasingly developing partnerships and leveraging new opportunities with business to accelerate progress towards achieving SDG 5, and our new Economic Development Strategy commits us to working with the private sector to deliver growth that is socially responsible and empowers women.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792789/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:17:27.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792789/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792789/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-11-20","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether he plans to consult businesses about how to measure progress on towards Sustainable Development Goal 5 on gender equality and women's empowerment.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","114716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792790","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-27","<p>We are currently in the process of agreeing the final draft of the evaluation. There is a standard 12 week clearance and formatting period from the time the final draft is agreed to publication. We will make the publication date available once it has been confirmed.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792790/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T16:45:56.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792790/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792790/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-20","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will set out the timetable for the publication of his Department's assessment of the yellow card early warning system for benefit sanctions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","114717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792791","Home Office","false","2017-11-27","<p>The Government does not collect information relating to the frequency of successful appeals against decisions taken by licensing committees to restrict the sale of cheap, super-strength alcohol.</p><p> </p><p>The Government keeps the Licensing Act 2003 under review and speaks regularly to police and licensing representatives to understand if there are any gaps in the legislation or whether there is a case for new powers.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792791/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T17:25:54.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792791/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792791/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-20","Licensing Laws","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of granting local authorities powers to reduce the frequency of successful appeals against decisions taken by licensing boards to restrict the sale of cheap, super-strength alcohol.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","114718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792792","Department for Transport","false","2017-11-28","<p>The Government continues to take Volkswagen’s actions in relation to diesel emissions extremely seriously and is working hard on behalf of UK consumers. Following pressure from the UK Government, Volkswagen Group now offer a ‘Trust Building Measure’ for all consumers that have had, and will have, the technical measure applied. This commits Volkswagen to respond reasonably and appropriately to every complaint which relates to the implementation of the service action. Officials have met with the Volkswagen Diesel Customer Forum to hear their concerns and plans for a further meeting in January 2018 are being finalised.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792792/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T10:28:05.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792792/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792792/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-11-20","Volkswagen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made in expediting compensation to vehicle owners affected by the Volkswagen emissions scandal since the debate in Westminster Hall on 20 April 2017 on emissions and vehicle type approval; whether such compensation will match that given to vehicle owners in the the US; and whether his Department has made an assessment of the heightened incidence of breakdowns and mechanical failures reported by the Volkswagen Diesel Customer Forum after updates have been completed.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","114719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792793","Department for Education","false","2017-11-24","<p>The Immigration Skills Charge is intended to address skills gaps in the workforce. The Home Office collect the Immigration Skills Charge as part of the visa sponsorship process and transfer it to the Exchequer, less an amount to cover the costs of collecting it. The population percentages underlying the Barnett formula are used by HM Treasury to determine the split of funding raised by the Immigration Skills Charge between the department and each of the devolved Administrations.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792793/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-24T12:48:40.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792793/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792793/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-11-20","Migrant Workers: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans his Department has for the allocation of funds raised by the Immigration Skills charge.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","114720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792794","Home Office","false","2017-11-23","<p>The Immigration Skills Charge (ISC), introduced on 6 April, is a charge paid by UK-based employers sponsoring non-EEA nationals under Tier 2, our main immigration work route.</p><p>The ISC is designed to incentivise employers to invest in training and upskilling the resident workforce. Income raised by the Charge will be used to address skills gaps in the UK workforce - which will be of benefit to businesses in the long term.</p><p>There is a flat rate of £1,000 per Tier 2 migrant sponsored per year but small or charitable sponsors already have a reduced rate of £364 per migrant per year.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792794/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-23T17:29:59.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792794/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792794/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-11-20","Migrant Workers: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the recommendations in the Recruitment & Employment Confederation’s report, Building the Post-Brexit Immigration System, whether the Government plans to exempt SMEs from the immigration skills charge.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","114721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792795","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-11-28","<p>We take hate crime in all its forms very seriously that is why the United Kingdom has some of the strongest hate crime legislation in the world. The increase in hate crime reported to Tell Mama in part reflects a greater encouragement and confidence around reporting as well as an increasing number of data sharing agreements with police forces.</p><p>Nevertheless, it is deplorable that any Muslim citizens should be subjected to abuse on account of their belief or appearance.</p><p>My Department works with Muslim communities through our anti-Muslim-hatred working group to address the problem of hate crime and to encourage greater reporting.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792795/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-28T17:25:41.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792795/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792795/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-11-20","Religious Hatred: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make an assessment of the potential implications for his policies of the Tell MAMA Annual Report for 2016 on Anti-Muslim Hatred; and what steps his Department plans to take to address the increase in the proportion of directly abusive and violent anti-Muslim incidents.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","114722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792796","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-27","<p>Including Employment and Support Allowance claimants in changes to SMI will save around £65 million in benefit expenditure each year.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792796/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T16:18:44.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792796/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792796/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-20","Employment and Support Allowance: Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate his Department has made of the annual savings to the public purse of including employment and support allowance claimants in the support mortgage interest changes due to take place in April 2018.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","114723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792797","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-27","<p>Estimates of ESA claimants in receipt of SMI, by conditionality group, are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>ESA Conditionality Group</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Caseload</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Assessment Phase</p></td><td><p>3,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Work Related Activity Group</p></td><td><p>9,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Support Group</p></td><td><p>38,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792797/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T16:25:57.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792797/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792797/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-20","Employment and Support Allowance: Support for Mortgage Interest","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in the (a) Support Group and (b) working group of employment support allowance claim Support Mortgage Interest.","false","Biography information for Jared O'Mara","Sheffield, Hallam","Jared O'Mara","114724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-27","<p>The Department does not collect administrative data on the proportion of employment and support allowance claimants who were also residents in supported housing in the last 12 months.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government recently announced plans for a new flexible funding approach for supported housing. As part of this it has launched two consultations seeking views on the details of the models.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/funding-for-supported-housing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/funding-for-supported-housing</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792798/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T16:34:40.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792798/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-20","Employment and Support Allowance: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of employment and support allowance claimants were also residents of supported housing in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","114725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792799","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-11-27","<p>The Department does not collect administrative data on the number and proportion of supported housing residents that also claim Employment and Support Allowance.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Government recently announced plans for a new flexible funding approach for supported housing. As part of this it has launched two consultations seeking views on the details of the models.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/funding-for-supported-housing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/funding-for-supported-housing</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792799/answer",,,,,,"2017-11-27T16:36:49.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792799/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/792799/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-11-20","Employment and Support Allowance: Supported Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of residents of supported housing claim Employment and Support Allowance.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","114726"
